<!-- FAQ -->

<section class="py-12 bg-slate-50">
<div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">

<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-8">Frequently Asked Questions — Raebareli Solar</h2>

<div class="space-y-4">

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-semibold">Which electricity company handles rooftop solar in Raebareli?</h3>
<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
Raebareli falls under <strong>MVVNL (Madhyanchal Vidyut Vitran Nigam Limited)</strong>, a subsidiary
of UPPCL. All net metering applications, bi-directional meter installations, and solar scheme
empanelment for Raebareli homeowners are processed through MVVNL.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-semibold">How do I apply for net metering in Raebareli?</h3>
<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
After installation by an MVVNL-empanelled installer, your installer submits the net metering
application to MVVNL on your behalf. MVVNL inspects the system and replaces your meter with a
bi-directional net meter. The process typically takes two to six weeks.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-semibold">Is PM Surya Ghar subsidy available in Raebareli?</h3>
<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
Yes. Raebareli homeowners with an MVVNL electricity connection are eligible. You must use an
MVVNL-empanelled installer and apply through pmsuryaghar.gov.in. Verify current subsidy
amounts and eligibility before applying.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-semibold">What solar system size suits most Raebareli homes?</h3>
<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
For typical Raebareli residential homes with monthly bills of ₹1,500–₹4,000, a 2kW to 3kW
on-grid system covers a significant portion of electricity needs. Households with air
conditioning use through summer often benefit from a 3kW system.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-semibold">How much does rooftop solar cost in Raebareli?</h3>
<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
Approximate pre-subsidy cost in Raebareli ranges from ₹60,000 to ₹80,000 per kW depending on
panel brand, inverter type, and installer. After the PM Surya Ghar central subsidy (up to
₹78,000 for 3kW), the net cost is significantly lower. Get quotes from at least two
MVVNL-empanelled installers before deciding.
</p>
</div>

<div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-2xl border">
<h3 class="font-semibold">Is Raebareli a good location for solar?</h3>
<p class="mt-2 text-slate-600 text-sm">
Yes. Raebareli receives approximately 5 to 5.5 peak sun hours per day on average —
well-suited for rooftop solar. Sunny, hot summers mean high solar output coincides with
peak electricity demand, making solar financially effective for most Raebareli homeowners.
</p>
</div>

</div>
</div>
</section>

